	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64153381"><p><div class="quote"><p>I have an idea for a cheap experiment.</p><p>Let's ground all climate change proponents for just a year...</p><p><b>ALL</b> climate meetings have to be virtual...absolutely NO flying anywhere to meet in person. Hell, no driving to meet in person, eh?</p><p>Let's see if we can see any changes in climate from all the fossil fuel burned by all this action?</p><p>Hell, just for fun, let's put them all on a "bug" or at least a meat free diet, like they propose for the rest of earth...monitor them strictly to make sure they don't sneak a McD's at 2am.....</p><p>I'm sure this would do a world of good, show everyone by example what can be done and the results of such.</p><p>I can't imagine those big conferences, or the Al Gore's or Klaus Schwabs of the world would object to it, no?</p></div><p>It was observed by NASA during covid lockdowns. <i>The COVID-19 pandemic and resulting limitations on travel and other economic sectors by countries around the globe drastically decreased air pollution and greenhouse gas emissions within just a few weeks. That sudden change gave scientists an unprecedented view of results that would take regulations years to achieve.</i>  <a href="https://climate.nasa.gov/news/3129/emission-reductions-from-pandemic-had-unexpected-effects-on-atmosphere/" title="nasa.gov">https://climate.nasa.gov/news/...</a> [nasa.gov]</p></div>
