	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64153535"><p><div class="quote"><p>if temps are rising then every year should be a new record</p></div><p>
No because of weather. While average over a year will reduce the fluctuations due to weather it will not eliminate them especially since there are single phenomena with global impact like El Nino. With an increasing climate temperature there will be an increased chance of setting a record each year and the faster the rate of increase the greater that chance becomes but it is not a certainty.</p></div>
	</div>

